    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Mounting Engine on Stand - Engine
        Preparation - Drain Engine Fluids
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Drain Engine Fluids</title>
        <figure id="f26501001" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh05/H05011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Coolant drain plug location</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a coolant drain pan beneath the coolant drain plug. Remove coolant drain plug (M18)
                and O-ring from the bottom of the oil system module. Open radiator cap to allow system to drain quicker.
                After draining coolant, install new O-ring on plug and install in module. Torque plug to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_S265APPB01.xml" xrefid="S265APPB01" appearance="hottext">standard torque
                    value</hotlnk>. Dispose of used coolant according to applicable laws.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26501001.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh06/H06085.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Draining the oil</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a oil drain pan beneath the oil drain plug to collect the oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pan drain plug (M25) and O-ring. Drain engine oil and dispose of used engine oil
                according to applicable laws.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard O-ring, inspect drain plug and replace if necessary. Place a new O-ring onto drain
                plug and install to oil pan. See
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_35.xml" xrefid="t01001" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
